# ðŸŒŸ **SQLWithIDC â€“ Day 18 Challenge**

## ðŸ§© **Challenge Question**

Create a comprehensive personnel and patient list showing: identifier (patient_id or staff_id),
full name, type ('Patient' or 'Staff'), and associated service.Include only those in 'surgery' or 'emergency' services.
Order by type, then service, then name.
  

## ðŸ’» **SQL Query**
  
(SELECT p.patient_id AS identifier,p.name AS full_name,'Patient' AS type,p.service
FROM patients p WHERE p.service IN ('surgery', 'emergency'))UNION
(SELECT s.staff_id AS identifier,s.staff_name AS full_name,'Staff' AS type,s.service
FROM staff s WHERE s.service IN ('surgery', 'emergency')) ORDER BY type, service, full_name;


--Practice questions
--1. Combine patient names and staff names into a single list.  
SELECT name AS full_name,'Patient' AS category FROM patients UNION SELECT staff_name AS full_name,
'Staff' AS category FROM staff ORDER BY full_name;

--2. Create a union of high satisfaction patients (>90) and low satisfaction patients (<50).
SELECT patient_id,name,satisfaction,'High Satisfaction' AS satisfaction_category
FROM patients WHERE satisfaction > 90 UNION ALL SELECT patient_id,name,satisfaction,
'Low Satisfaction' AS satisfaction_category FROM patients WHERE satisfaction < 50;

--3. List all unique names from both patients and staff tables.
SELECT name FROM patients UNION SELECT staff_name FROM staff;

